= Self-evaluation

The work was distributed as equally as possible between all the members of the group. We tried to divide the tasks in a fair way, both for the report and for the final presentation.

Each member was responsible for a specific part of the project, but we did not work completely independently. We tried to help each other whenever it was necessary, especially when one part of the design affected another part of the system.

Communication inside the group was also important during the project. We tried to stay in continuous contact in order to keep the work synchronized, avoid repeated content and make the report coherent. This was especially relevant because the analog front-end, the ADC stage, the FPGA acquisition, the power supply and the software are strongly connected.

For the report, we divided the work by sections and later reviewed the document together to improve the structure, correct inconsistencies and make the writing style more uniform. For the presentation, we also divided the slides by topic, but we coordinated the content so that the explanation followed a clear order and there was no excessive overlap between speakers.

From our point of view, the group worked in an organized and collaborative way. The final result is not only the sum of individual parts, but a common design in which the different blocks of the system are connected and justified together.